<blockquote>
	<p><i><b>Ubiquitous computing</b> is roughly the <b>opposite of virtual reality</b>. Where virtual reality puts people inside a computer-generated world, ubiquitous computing forces the computer to <b>live out here in the world with people.</b></i></p>
	<br><p>-Mark Weiser</p>
	&nbsp;
</blockquote>

